Commentary Text: Ashwin to Uthappa, out Caught&Bowled!! Oh dear! CSK are falling away in a heap - the middle-order hadn't been tested until today, it's coming apart tonight. Nicely flighted on off, was the carrom ball and Uthappa didn't spot it - was looking to swipe it over mid-wicket, closed the bat-face and got a big leading edge, right back at the bowler. Pant went for the catch, but it was Ashwin who called for it, settled under it, went reverse cupped and held on. CSK need to work out a better plan and this is the right time for them to brood over as the players take the strategic break. Uthappa c and b Ashwin 19(19) [4s-1]
